snippet.textDisplay: What really annoys me is the fact that everyone cries for the return of Rohail Hyatt who was brilliant, no doubt but if you were to really look at his work you would find multiple experimentational songs as well. For every Jugni etc. There was also Kir Kir by Sajjad Ali which was country music! Imagine country music in Coke Studio but he took that creative risk. So appreciate creativity and diversity and brush up on your coke studio memories. This song is amazing and a departure from the usual Sufi Fusion. Ali Hamza is amazing and his vibe over here is so infectious I could listen to this all day
